3. Custom TFM-Models (Research)

  - Usage: Physiological Research.
  - Role: These are smaller, specialized models trained on the "Complete
    Lifespan Neural Network."
  - Function: They compare the live vector from Nodes 17–26 against the Baseline
    Research. They look for "Anomalies" (e.g., a vascular pattern that suggests
