V. How the Data Retains Integrity

Because every token and vector is "Vectored off" the DNA Signature, the LLM
doesn't actually "know" Chase. It only knows the Vector State.

  - The LLM sees: Vector_X is in State_Y.
  - The Vault (Local) knows: Vector_X is Chase_Ringquist.

This separation ensures that the Gaming Industry can use your "Reflex Tokens"
for a high-speed match, or the Research Industry can use your "Vascular Tokens"
for a health study, without any of them ever being able to access the original
DNA Root or disturb the Frozen Baseline of the corpus.
